# What other steps is the Ukrainian government taking to secure sovereignty in the face of Russian aggression besides withdrawal of Russian forces from the west bank of the Dnipro River?

## Summary
The Ukrainian government is taking further steps to secure its sovereignty in the face of Russian aggression. Defense Minister Sergey Shoigu has ordered a withdrawal of Russian forces from the west bank of the Dnipro River in Kherson region <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font>. The defense ministry is requisitioning several energy and manufacturing companies "of strategic importance" <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font> in order to ensure sufficient supplies for the military. Ukraine is ready to negotiate an end to the war with a future Russian leader but not Putin <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. Ukrainian forces have disabled bridges across the Dnipro and attacked Russian supply lines <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font>, and have fought the Russian military "to a standstill" <font color=#FF3399>[4]</font>. On November 10, Snihurivka settlement was liberated by the 131st separate scout battalion <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font>.

